comment_regular_data.body:
@KarlEricsson so if I understand what you want correctly (sorry if I'm missing something) is only showing `virtual_lines` for the current line and `virtual_text` everywhere else.

Then you can have something like:
```lua
vim.diagnostic.config {
  virtual_text = {
    format = function(diag)
      local lnum = api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[1] - 1
      -- Don't use the virtual text handler for diagnostics at the current line.
      if diag.lnum == lnum then return nil end
      return diag.message
    end
  },
  virtual_lines = { current_line = true }
}
```

Note that I haven't tested this, but I expect it to work.
